Autofocus

The Focus-Point Display


The focus-point display varies with the option selected for AF
mode.


Focus frames are shown by small squares (□), focus zones by the large squares. ● The dimensions of ZONE CUSTOM 1, ZONE CUSTOM 2, and ZONE CUSTOM 3 can be selected using MF AF/MF SETTING > ZONE AF CUSTOM SETTING.
AF mode SINGLE POINT CJ ZONE
WIDE/TRACKING □ 0 □ □
Number of points avail- Choose from zones with Position focus frame over able can be selected using 7x7,5 x 5, or 3 X 3 focus subject you want to track AF AF/MF SETTING > points or from ZONE using continuous AF. MF NUMBER OF FOCUS CUSTOM 1, ZONE POINTS. CUSTOM 2, and ZONE CUSTOM 3.
Autofocus Although the camera boasts a high-precision autofocus system, it may be unable to focus on the subjects listed below. ● Very shiny subjects such as mirrors or car bodies. ● Subjects photographed through a window or other reflective object. ● Dark subjects and subjects that absorb rather than reflect light, such as hair or fur. ● Insubstantial subjects, such as smoke or flame. ● Subjects that show little contrast with the background. ● Subjects positioned in front of or behind a high-contrast object that is also in the focus frame (for example, a subject photographed against a backdrop of highly contrasting elements).
